<BaseLayout
  title="Custom Tape Measures: What Importers Need to Know Before Ordering"
  description="Learn what importers should confirm before ordering custom tape measures, including logo, shell color, tape length, blade, MOQ, packaging, and lead time."
  path="/blog/custom-tape-measures-guide/"
>
  <article class="article">
    <p class="eyebrow">Importer guide</p>
    <h1>Custom Tape Measures: What Importers Need to Know Before Ordering</h1>
    <p>Custom tape measures can support retail, promotional, distributor, and private-label programs. Before requesting a quote, buyers should prepare the details that affect cost, samples, production, and delivery.</p>
    <h2>Product specifications</h2>
    <p>Confirm tape length, shell size, tape blade material, lock style, hook style, and whether the product needs a belt clip or wrist strap. These details help the supplier recommend a realistic model.</p>
    <h2>Branding options</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Logo on the case or label area</li>
      <li>Custom shell color</li>
      <li>Printed tape blade details</li>
      <li>Retail packaging artwork</li>
      <li>Barcode, carton mark, and private-label information</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>MOQ and lead time</h2>
    <p>MOQ may change based on color, printing, packaging, and production complexity. Lead time also depends on sample approval, packaging artwork approval, and order volume.</p>
    <h2>How to send a better RFQ</h2>
    <p>Include quantity, market, logo file, packaging preference, target price, delivery date, and any reference product photos. A detailed RFQ helps the supplier respond faster and more accurately.</p>
  </article>
  <CTA title="Ready to order custom tape measures?" primaryLabel="Get Custom Solution" />
</BaseLayout>
